The paper deals with optimization of submodular functions, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of stochastic gradient descent and its variants also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and stochastic optimization (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) in the sense that it deals with maximizing coverage functions, which are a type of information measure.
